INDICATOR_NAME: Domestic private health expenditure per capita (current US$)
SOURCE_NOTE: Current private expenditures on health per capita expressed in current US dollars. Domestic private sources include funds from households, corporations and non-profit organizations. Such expenditures can be either prepaid to voluntary health insurance or paid directly to healthcare providers.
SOURCE_ORGANIZATION: World Health Organization Global Health Expenditure database (http://apps.who.int/nha/database). The data was retrieved on January 30, 2022.
